{"id":"dung-hill","term":"Dung-hill","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>To sit on a, was a sign of the deepest dejection (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 2:8\">1 Sam. 2:8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 113:7\">Ps. 113:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Lamentations 4:5\">Lam. 4:5</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Samuel 2:8","Psalms 113:7","Lamentations 4:5"]}